		<div class="comment_text"><p>Ray,</p><p>Has the car ever set without being started for more than 6 weeks?  Gas can go bad, especially if the quality of the gas was not top notch to begin with.  Things can happen like getting water in the gas or accidental contamination at the gas station when the delivery driver accidentally puts some diesel or kerosene into the gas storage tanks (the stations usually have hardware methods to prevent this from happening).</p><p>If your car (or lawnmower or anything that runs on gas) sits for extended periods you'll probably need to put in a gas stabilizer like Sta-Bil (<a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldeagle.com%2Fsta-bil%2F%29%3Aou-6VNJwF0dHmSK-TaOVAnoTWyE&amp;cuid=3321886" rel="nofollow noopener" title="http://www.goldeagle.com/sta-bil/)">http://www.goldeagle.com/st...</a>.  I hope everything works out.</p></div>
